This product includes software originally developed as part of:

  - codex-plugin-cc (https://github.com/openai/codex-plugin-cc) by OpenAI
    — the original plugin architecture, command patterns, and skill structure.

  - opencode-plugin-cc (https://github.com/tasict/opencode-plugin-cc) by tasict
    — the OpenCode adaptation this project is directly forked from.

Portions of the hardening and fixes in this distribution were harvested from
the following forks (Apache License 2.0), with thanks:

  - suharvest/opencode-plugin-cc — background-job self-heal, race-condition
    fixes, state-dir isolation, and the recursive-delegation safety header.

  - JohnnyVicious/opencode-plugin-cc — the node:http workaround for undici's
    hidden body timeout, review-handler --model threading, and fixes ported
    from openai/codex-plugin-cc.

Modifications made in this fork (per Apache License 2.0, Section 4(b)) include,
among others: routing the model field as a {providerID, modelID} object for
current OpenCode REST versions; a node:http prompt transport that bypasses
undici's 300s body timeout; automatic rejection of un-answerable permission
prompts in headless dispatch; a filesystem lock around job-state writes;
correct read-only derivation from --agent plan; provider-list parsing for the
{all, default, connected} response shape; verbatim prompt forwarding; and an
expanded test suite covering the previously-untested modules.

Additional modifications in v2.0.1: OpenCode-side token/cost reporting on every
dispatch path (getSessionUsage); a PID start-time ownership fingerprint so
cancel/reconcile never signal a recycled pid; pid tracking for detached
background workers; opt-in git-worktree isolation (--worktree) with a
temp-file patch round-trip; a wait-and-result blocking dispatch made the
default rescue path; and removal of the dead --scope review flag.

Additional modifications in v2.0.2 (from an adversarial multi-model review of
the codebase): a start-time fingerprint on the file-lock owner token so a live
holder's lock is never stolen on age; cancel re-reads job status before
overwriting it; fail-fast when a worker cannot be spawned; parse guards so a
value option never swallows a following flag; git add/diff exit-code checks and
subdirectory-aware cwd in the worktree round-trip; a total timeout with SIGKILL
escalation in runCommand; and lenient numeric-string parsing of session cost.

